Hi everyone,<br>
My name is Veiovis and I'm a 53rd cleric with Clan Nan Duibhre.<br>
I wanted to post a THANK YOU to all of BC but especially......<br>
Balludar, Ecosys, Thorvan, Glia, Centuri, Intuity, Silfe, Kannushi, Kiari, and Mythreal &lt;I really hope I did not mis-spell anyones name and please forgive me if I left anyone out&gt;.<br>
You were all very helpful and incrediably frendly last night. Not only is that a credit to those of you who were there, but to the entire guild. There fore....Blood Circle.. I salute you!!<br>
&lt;V attempts a formal bow....loses his balance, falls and in the ensuing melee of trying to stand has lost all dramatic effect; as well as a few peices of armor&gt;<br>
For those of you who were not there.... <br>
I was camping the Tormented's for their skulls in TM as part of the &quot;Shield of Bane Warding&quot; quest.<br>
&lt;V uses his foot indiscretely to push the remaining armor on the floor, behind him and out of sight&gt;<br>
I had collected 7 when my oldest son had a nightmare and I walked away from the computer.  Upon returing I found myself at my bind point...killed by none other than a Tormented.<br>
&lt;V suddenly realizes he is holding his dollie (Paw of Opalla) and immediately throws it into the darkness surrounding the light.  Continuing as if nothing had happened.......&gt;<br>
After a 40 minute CR I roll up on the camp to find Balludar and Ecosys there. I sigh and resign myself to logging early because I know I've lost the camp.<br>
&lt;V's attachment to his dollie is most apparent.  His eyes constantly darting toward the direction he threw the paw.<br>
Beads of sweat form on his brow. Seems edgy and distracted.  Truely pathetic&gt;<br>
However.....after rezzing myself<br>
&lt;V dives into the darkness in the direction he tossed the paw.  Returns with his arms crossed but obviously holding something&gt;<br>
I said hello and soon the conversation turned to my having one skull to go.<br>
Balludar and Ecosys were both immediate and insistant on my looting the next Tormented spawn.  This type of friendship is, unfortunately, all too uncommon on our server.  It was most refreshing and appreciated to be offered such a gift.<br>
BUT...that was not the end of the encounter!!<br>
After what seemed like a short eternity.....<br>
&lt;Being a Dwarf of &quot;very little brain&quot;....he is oblivious to having put &quot;short&quot; and &quot;eternity&quot; togeather and therefore confused what few people he was capable of communicating with&gt;<br>
the Tormented spawn and I loot the 8th skull needed for the quest.<br>
Now.....now Balludar invites me to begin quest and get the fights out of the way.  As my dwarven luck would have it.... you had a couple of groups already doing the quest and all seemed very happy to have me along and help me with the mobs. <br>
I was able to finish most of the quest last night and mostly due to your guild.<br>
&lt;A tear rolls down V cheek....either due to the emotion of the moment OR because he just realized be fractured a rib diving for that silly doll of his&gt;<br>
Thank you again and please do not hesitate to call on me.  I owe you all BIG and the debt is one that I will not forget.<br>
&lt;V gathers his bits of fallen armor, stuffs them into a backpack and exits stage left.&gt;<br>
